    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for poppler.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 10.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "Poppler is a Portable Document Format (PDF) rendering library, used by applications such as Evince.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* poppler: Out-of-Bounds Read in Poppler (CVE-2025-32365)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
